******
[2]
Date: Thu 10 Nov 2022
Source: Excelsior [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/brote-de-meningitis-en-durango-fue-provocado-por-hongo-hay-41-casos-y-3-muertos/1551650


The cases of aseptic meningitis in Durango were caused by a fungus, so immediate treatment is instructed for patients and to continue with comprehensive care for families.

The Secretary of Health, Irasema Kondo Padilla, confirmed the above and stressed that there are currently 41 confirmed cases and 3 deaths [now 4].

The results of the studies of etiological factors determined the cause of illness of people from various private hospitals in Durango; meanwhile, the Cofepris (Federal Commission for the Protection Against Sanitary Risks) continues with the investigations to establish the mechanism of contamination.

When the cause of this condition is known, the treatment of the patients begins. It was recognized that it is expensive, but at this time the health of the patients is considered, and comprehensive care will be provided with hospitalization, treatment, and medications, as well as the necessary requirements for family members.

Kondo Padilla explained that the results of various laboratories of the Health Sector and the National Institute of Medical Sciences and Nutrition "Salvador Zubirán" coincided in the presence of a fungus in the cases of affected patients; confirmation of the results from INDRE (Institute of Epidemiological Diagnosis and Reference) is also expected.

As of today [10 Nov 2022], there are 41 confirmed cases of patients with aseptic meningitis, 40 women and one man; 3 unfortunate deaths are reported, the last registered after medical attention was provided at the IMSS hospital.

[Byline: Alma Gudiño]

